        "Description/Abstract": "A growing number of states are requiring that corporations include unitary business income from foreign \u201ctax havens\u201d in their water\u2019s edge combined returns.  In this article, we discuss the emerging state approaches to foreign tax haven income, examine the critical reaction to those approaches, and put those approaches in the context of prior state attempts to protect their corporate tax revenue streams from income shifting or overly generous (in the states\u2019 view) federal corporate income tax policy.    ",
